    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You may use <code>java.util.Date</code> class and then use <code>SimpleDateFormat</code> to format the <code>Date</code>.</p>\n\n<pre><code>Date date=new Date(millis);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>We can use <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/datetime/index.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">java.time</a> package (tutorial) - DateTime APIs introduced in the Java SE 8. </p>\n\n<pre><code>var instance = java.time.Instant.ofEpochMilli(millis);\nvar localDateTime = java.time.LocalDateTime\n                        .ofInstant(instance, java.time.ZoneId.of(\"Asia/Kolkata\"));\nvar zonedDateTime = java.time.ZonedDateTime\n                            .ofInstant(instance,java.time.ZoneId.of(\"Asia/Kolkata\"));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><code>// Format the date</code></p>\n\n<pre><code>var formatter = java.time.format.DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern(\"u-M-d hh:mm:ss a O\");\nvar string = zonedDateTime.format(formatter);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
