    "body" : "<p>The easiest way to do this is to use the <a href=\"http://joda-time.sourceforge.net/apidocs/org/joda/time/DateTime.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Joda DateTime class</a> and specify both the timestamp in milliseconds and the DateTimeZone you want.</p>\n\n<p>I strongly recommend avoiding the built-in Java Date and Calendar classes; they're terrible.</p>\n"
